Usage: install [options] [[--tarball] FILE]

An installer for SmartGit's tarballs in Debian/Ubuntu/Mint

Includes uninstall script. Tested with v3.0.4

Options:
-h|--help  - show this page.
-q|--quiet - supress informative messages.

--system
--user
	choose system-wide or per-user install. Default is user

--exec=NAME
	executable name, also used as a prefix for for naming the
	install directory, icon and .desktop files. Default "smartgit"

--prefix=DIR
	parent of the install directory. Default is "/opt"

--name=NAME
	friendly application name, for menu entries. Default "SmartGit"

--tarball FILE
	the tar.gz install archive downloaded from SmartGit's website.
	If none is provided, a menu will show currently downloaded files.

--uninstall
	Uninstall SmartGit. Combine with --system, --exec and --prefix to
	uninstall from a custom install

